{"case_id": "case-002-d2-03", "container": "D", "pipeline_depth": 2, "message": "Type 2 DM, eGFR 55, scheduled for CT with IV contrast tomorrow. On metformin 1000mg BID.", "latency_ms": 6897, "llm_calls": 2, "tokens_in": 218, "tokens_out": 229, "cost_usd": 0.0001701, "task_success": true, "abstained": false, "answer": "Given the patient's eGFR of 55 mL/min and scheduled CT with IV contrast, it is recommended to discontinue metformin at the time of, or prior to, contrast administration. Metformin should be withheld for 48 hours post-procedure. Renal function (eGFR) must be re-evaluated 48 hours after contrast administration, and metformin may be restarted if renal function is stable and has returned to baseline. This strategy mitigates the risk of metformin-associated lactic acidosis (per established clinical guidelines).", "tool_calls": 0, "hop_metrics": [{"hop": "vector_ingress", "latency_ms": 5, "llm_calls": 0, "tokens_in": 0, "tokens_out": 0, "tool_calls": 0}, {"hop": "cache_gate", "latency_ms": 0, "llm_calls": 0, "tokens_in": 0, "tokens_out": 0, "tool_calls": 0}, {"hop": "intake", "latency_ms": 1848, "llm_calls": 1, "tokens_in": 65, "tokens_out": 123, "tool_calls": 0}, {"hop": "writer", "latency_ms": 5039, "llm_calls": 1, "tokens_in": 153, "tokens_out": 106, "tool_calls": 0}], "embed_count": 2, "cache_hit": false, "cache_score": 0.0, "variant": "novel", "error": null}
